      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS LEOPATRA NZ (3) scored for the fourth time in her last five starts when leading to cruise home by 17m in a heat of this series at this circuit and distance last week. Hard not to be impressed by that and she draws to to push forward again so looks the one to beat. SOVEREIGN JEWEL (1) is in good form having dug deep for narrow wins in her last two outings. Draws for a soft run so could land the hat trick. IM CATEGORY FIVE (9) will be peaking now having placed in her last three outings. Draws wide so may need luck but has yet to miss the top-three in eight attempts at this circuit and distance. Each way hope along with CRUNCHNSIP (10) who draws for a trail and has gone under narrowly in her last two outings, missing SOVEREIGN JEWEL by a nose last week.",
